<p>Simple example:</p>  <pre><code>public class Food {     public virtual void Eat()     {         StuffInMouth();     } }  public class Fruit : Food {     // Nothing here yet, but likely could be in the future     // Is this bad from a .NET/C# style guidelines perspective? }  public class Apple : Fruit {     public virtual void Eat()     {         Clean();         base.Eat();     } }  public class Orange : Fruit {     public virtual void Eat()     {         Peel();         base.Eat();     } } </code></pre>